CONFERENCE PROGRAM AND REGISTRATION INFORMATION

This posting details the important information about  the  USENIX
Winter 1994 Technical Conference, including:

- Conference  schedule  of activities and events
- Vendor Display & Product Demonstrations
- Special hotel rates and airfares --  how  to  make your reservations
- Upcoming USENIX Symposia and Conferences
- How to register for the conference
- Conference Registration Form

Learn results from the latest research and investigate  important
developments  in UNIX in its many flavors and in related areas of
advanced technology.   Join  your  fellow  professionals  at  the
USENIX Winter 1994 Technical Conference in:
*refereed and invited technical presentations
*expert-led full-day tutorials 
*informal Birds-of-a-Feather Sessions
*demonstrations of products and services, and
*other conference gatherings.

At USENIX in San Francisco, system  researchers  and  developers,
system  managers  and network administrators, programmers and ap-
plications developers, technical support staff and managers, edu-
cators and their students will gather to explore questions of im-
mediate importance to advanced computing systems  management  and
innovation.  Professionals from within the "open" systems commun-
ity, the "downsizing" community, the PC  environment,  and  those
moving  from  VM/CMS  or VMS to UNIX will share ideas, experience
and, learn of the latest technological developments.

The USENIX Association's two technical conferences are well known
as  leading  forums for the communication of new research and the
investigation of important developments in UNIX or UNIX-like sys-
tems  as  well as in the rapidly developing technologies.relevant
to those working in advanced computing environments.

